{"document":"=============================================\n\nAuthor: Ascendion AAVA\n\nCreated on:\n\nDescription: Bronze layer ETL pipeline orchestrator loading 12 target tables with audit logging and error handling\n\n=============================================\n\n# 1. Overview of Program\n\nThis Oracle PL/SQL stored procedure orchestrates the bronze layer ETL pipeline by sequentially invoking 12 individual table load procedures, each processing data from source to bronze layer tables. The procedure implements comprehensive audit logging, batch tracking, execution time monitoring, and centralized error handling to ensure data integrity and traceability across the entire bronze layer data loading process.\n\n# 2. Code Structure and Design\n\n- Declares procedure bronze.usp_Load_bronze_Layer_Full with no parameters\n- Declares 17 local variables for procedure name, timestamps, execution metrics, error details, row counts, table counts, current user, and batch ID\n- Initializes batch ID using current timestamp formatted as 'YYYY-MM-DD HH24:MI:SS.FF3'\n- Logs pipeline start information including start time, executing user, and batch ID using DBMS_OUTPUT\n- Invokes bronze.usp_Load_bz_New_Monthly_HC_Report for table loading with batch ID parameter\n- Invokes bronze.usp_Load_bz_SchTask for table loading with batch ID parameter\n- Invokes bronze.usp_Load_bz_Hiring_Initiator_Project_Info for table loading with batch ID parameter\n- Invokes bronze.usp_Load_bz_Timesheet_New for table loading with batch ID parameter\n- Invokes bronze.usp_Load_bz_report_392_all for table loading with batch ID parameter\n- Invokes bronze.usp_Load_bz_vw_billing_timesheet_daywise_ne for table loading with batch ID parameter\n- Invokes bronze.usp_Load_bz_vw_consultant_timesheet_daywise for table loading with batch ID parameter\n- Invokes bronze.usp_Load_bz_DimDate for table loading with batch ID parameter\n- Invokes bronze.usp_Load_bz_holidays_Mexico for table loading with batch ID parameter\n- Invokes bronze.usp_Load_bz_holidays_Canada for table loading with batch ID parameter\n- Invokes bronze.usp_Load_bz_holidays for table loading with batch ID parameter\n- Invokes bronze.usp_Load_bz_holidays_India for table loading with batch ID parameter\n- Increments tables processed counter after each procedure invocation\n- Executes SELECT query on bronze.bz_Audit_Log to aggregate successful table counts and total rows inserted filtered by batch ID and SUCCESS status\n- Executes SELECT query on bronze.bz_Audit_Log to aggregate failed table counts and total rows failed filtered by batch ID and FAILED status\n- Calculates total rows processed by summing inserted and failed rows\n- Calculates execution time by extracting day, hour, minute, and second components from timestamp difference\n- Logs completion summary including end time, execution time, tables processed, tables succeeded, tables failed, total rows inserted, and total rows failed using DBMS_OUTPUT\n- Inserts master audit record into bronze.bz_Audit_Log with aggregated metrics for the entire pipeline execution\n- Commits transaction\n- Implements exception handler to capture error details using SQLERRM and SQLCODE\n- Logs error information including error number, severity, state, line, and message using DBMS_OUTPUT in exception block\n- Inserts error audit record into bronze.bz_Audit_Log with failure status and error message in exception block\n- Commits transaction in exception block\n- Raises application error with captured error message using RAISE_APPLICATION_ERROR\n\n# 3. Data Flow and Processing Logic\n\n```text\n+------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+\n| START            | -> | Initialize       | -> | Log Pipeline     | -> | Load Table 1     |\n| Procedure        |    | Variables &      |    | Start Info       |    | bz_New_Monthly   |\n|                  |    | Batch ID         |    |                  |    | _HC_Report       |\n+------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+\n                                                                                          |\n                                                                                          v\n+------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+\n| Load Table 5     | <- | Load Table 4     | <- | Load Table 3     | <- | Load Table 2     |\n| bz_report_392    |    | bz_Timesheet     |    | bz_Hiring        |    | bz_SchTask       |\n| _all             |    | _New             |    | _Initiator       |    |                  |\n+------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+\n                  |\n                  v\n+------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+\n| Load Table 6     | -> | Load Table 7     | -> | Load Table 8     | -> | Load Table 9     |\n| bz_vw_billing    |    | bz_vw_consultant |    | bz_DimDate       |    | bz_holidays      |\n| _timesheet       |    | _timesheet       |    |                  |    | _Mexico          |\n+------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+\n                                                                                          |\n                                                                                          v\n+------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+\n| Aggregate Audit  | <- | Load Table 12    | <- | Load Table 11    | <- | Load Table 10    |\n| Statistics from  |    | bz_holidays      |    | bz_holidays      |    | bz_holidays      |\n| bz_Audit_Log     |    | _India           |    |                  |    | _Canada          |\n+------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+\n                  |\n                  v\n+------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+\n| Calculate        | -> | Log Completion   | -> | Insert Master    | -> | Commit           |\n| Execution Time   |    | Summary          |    | Audit Record     |    | Transaction      |\n+------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+\n                                                                                          |\n                                                                                          v\n+------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+\n| END              | <- | Re-raise Error   | <- | Insert Error     | <- | Exception        |\n| Procedure        |    |                  |    | Audit Record     |    | Handler          |\n+------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+\n```\n\n# 4. Data Mapping\n\n| Target Object Name | Target Attribute Name | Source Object Name | Source Attribute Name | Remarks |\n|--------------------|-----------------------|--------------------|-----------------------|---------|\n| bronze.bz_Audit_Log | source_table | Literal | 'source_layer.*' | 1 to 1 mapping |\n| bronze.bz_Audit_Log | target_table | Literal | 'bronze.*' | 1 to 1 mapping |\n| bronze.bz_Audit_Log | load_timestamp | Variable | v_StartTime | 1 to 1 mapping |\n| bronze.bz_Audit_Log | start_timestamp | Variable | v_StartTime | 1 to 1 mapping |\n| bronze.bz_Audit_Log | end_timestamp | Variable | v_EndTime | 1 to 1 mapping |\n| bronze.bz_Audit_Log | processed_by | Variable | v_CurrentUser | 1 to 1 mapping |\n| bronze.bz_Audit_Log | processing_time | Variable | v_ExecutionTime | Derived attribute |\n| bronze.bz_Audit_Log | status | Variable | v_OverallStatus | 1 to 1 mapping |\n| bronze.bz_Audit_Log | records_processed | Variable | v_TotalRowsProcessed | Derived attribute |\n| bronze.bz_Audit_Log | records_inserted | Variable | v_TotalRowsInserted | Aggregation rule |\n| bronze.bz_Audit_Log | records_failed | Variable | v_TotalRowsFailed | Aggregation rule |\n| bronze.bz_Audit_Log | batch_id | Variable | v_BatchID | 1 to 1 mapping |\n| bronze.bz_Audit_Log | load_type | Literal | 'FULL_REFRESH_ALL_TABLES' | 1 to 1 mapping |\n| bronze.bz_Audit_Log | created_date | Function | SYSTIMESTAMP | Function rule |\n\n# 5. Complexity Analysis\n\n| Category | Measurement |\n|----------|-------------|\n| Number of Transformations | 0 |\n| Number of ETL Processes | 12 |\n| Number of Target Tables / Objects | 13 |\n| Number of Source Tables / Objects | 1 |\n| Number of Data Loads | 12 |\n| Number of JOIN Operations | 0 |\n| Number of Aggregation Operations | 4 |\n| Number of Sorting Operations | 0 |\n| Number of Cursors | 0 |\n| Number of Loops | 0 |\n| Conditional Logic Blocks | 0 |\n| Error Handling Blocks | 1 |\n| Logging/Audit Mechanisms | 3 |\n| External Dependencies | 12 |\n| System Integrations | 0 |\n| Overall Complexity Score (0–100) | 45 |\n\n# 6. Sensitive and Privacy Data Assessment\n\nNo sensitive data found\n\n# 7. Key Outputs\n\n- bronze.bz_New_Monthly_HC_Report\n- bronze.bz_SchTask\n- bronze.bz_Hiring_Initiator_Project_Info\n- bronze.bz_Timesheet_New\n- bronze.bz_report_392_all\n- bronze.bz_vw_billing_timesheet_daywise_ne\n- bronze.bz_vw_consultant_timesheet_daywise\n- bronze.bz_DimDate\n- bronze.bz_holidays_Mexico\n- bronze.bz_holidays_Canada\n- bronze.bz_holidays\n- bronze.bz_holidays_India\n- bronze.bz_Audit_Log\n\n# 8. API Cost Calculations\n\nAPI cost for this call: 0.0000 USD\n\nCalculation method: This is a stored procedure execution within Oracle database. No external API calls are made. All operations are internal database procedure invocations and SQL operations, which do not incur API costs in the context of cloud service API pricing."}